rg/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=stevel%40apache.org","name":"stevel@apache.org","key":"stevel@apache.org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513"},"displayName":"Steve Loughran","active":true,"timeZone":"Europe/London"},"created":"2013-08-13T00:19:38.708+0000","updated":"2013-08-13T00:19:38.708+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12663157/comment/13737610","id":"13737610","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=stevel%40apache.org","name":"stevel@apache.org","key":"stevel@apache.org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513"},"displayName":"Steve Loughran","active":true,"timeZone":"Europe/London"},"body":"What could be done is get the class, not cast it, but instead call {{FileSystem.concat()}}, expecting an {{UnsupportedOperationException}} if it isn't implemented, and downgrade that to an {{exit(-1)}}. That way: FS independent, and fails with some meaningful message. If anyone did ever implement concat on other filesystems, then it could get used.\n\nEven so, it is {{HDFSConcat}} for a reason: there is no expectation that it works elsewhere","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=stevel%40apache.org","name":"stevel@apache.org","key":"stevel@apache.org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=stevel%40apache.org&avatarId=16513"},"displayName":"Steve Loughran","active":true,"timeZone":"Europe/London"},"created":"2013-08-13T00:22:27.630+0000","updated":"2013-08-13T00:22:27.630+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12663157/comment/13737706","id":"13737706","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=lionghosthop","name":"lionghosthop","key":"lionghosthop","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Leo","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"Now, the problem is that it always uses the default fs even I specify hdfs paths as follows\n\njava org.apache.hadoop.hdfs.tools.HDFSConcat hdfs:///a hdfs:///b","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=lionghosthop","name":"lionghosthop","key":"lionghosthop","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=